<div id="content">
<h1>Raúl Díaz García</h1> 

<p>e-mail: rdiazgar (at) uci.edu<br>
   office: 4209 Donald Bren Hall</p>

<p>I'm a third year PhD student at <a href="http://www.uci.edu/">UC Irvine</a>, where I'm advised by professor <a href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~fowlkes/">Charless Fowlkes</a> at the <a href="http://vision.ics.uci.edu/">Computer Vision group.</a></p>

<p>My research is focused on improving object detection by finding geometric context cues. In particular,
I investigate how structure from motion and multi-view stereo can help in the world of scene understanding.</p>

<p></p>

